1
00:00:35,039 --> 00:00:35,560
An Xiang.

2
00:00:35,799 --> 00:00:37,119
An Xiang, are you okay?

3
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:39,000
It's fine, you're awake now.

4
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:47,079
Godfather, he...

5
00:00:49,479 --> 00:00:51,600
An Xiang, are you alright?

6
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:03,920
An Xiang, whatever you just saw,

7
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:05,079
none of it was real.

8
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:07,439
What on earth is going on?

9
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:09,359
You were poisoned.

10
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:11,959
Poisoned?

11
00:01:15,079 --> 00:01:16,799
So I was poisoned too?

12
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,640
Alright, alright.

13
00:01:41,599 --> 00:01:43,439
An Xiang, drink this.

14
00:01:43,959 --> 00:01:45,120
It's an antidote.

15
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,799
After ingesting those poisonous mushrooms,

16
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,640
people start hallucinating.

17
00:01:49,239 --> 00:01:50,040
Drink up.

18
00:01:52,439 --> 00:01:53,680
Miss He,

19
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,560
what... what is this stuff?

20
00:01:57,719 --> 00:01:58,920
Didn't Old Lu just say?

21
00:01:59,159 --> 00:02:00,120
It's an antidote.

22
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,159
Drink it, you'll be fine.

23
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:05,599
Uncle Min, you drink it.

24
00:02:06,239 --> 00:02:07,079
It's not bitter.

25
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:11,199
Clap your hands together,

26
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:14,879
Fine, Fatty, I'll drink it.

27
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,199
This is called Paris polyphylla.

28
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:19,479
It has seven leaves in a ring,

29
00:02:19,479 --> 00:02:20,719
with a flower blooming in the center.

30
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,919
They say even in the wild,

31
00:02:22,919 --> 00:02:23,960
if you're bitten by a venomous snake,

32
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:24,840
this can neutralize the venom.

33
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:26,719
But we didn't eat any poisonous mushrooms.

34
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:29,560
Mushroom spores are floating all over this cave.

35
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,800
On top of that, the light is dim,

36
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,039
so I didn't pay attention.

37
00:02:32,199 --> 00:02:33,280
All of us

38
00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:35,400
had hallucinations, right?

39
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,120
So why are you fine?

40
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,919
What's there to question?

41
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:41,240
Everyone has a different physical constitution.

42
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:42,560
Look at Old Chen,

43
00:02:42,719 --> 00:02:43,879
strong as an ox.

44
00:02:43,879 --> 00:02:46,639
Old Chen's got capillary hyperplasia.

45
00:02:47,280 --> 00:02:48,800
Uncle Min's got a big eye on him too,

46
00:02:49,479 --> 00:02:51,240
so shouldn't he have stayed clear-headed?

47
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,840
And yet he was still all twisted up.

48
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,599
Nonsense.

49
00:02:53,599 --> 00:02:55,159
Did he end up in your arms in the end?

50
00:02:56,159 --> 00:02:58,719
Can we please drop this subject?

51
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,439
Chen Youxi,

52
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:03,319
what actually just happened?

53
00:03:06,599 --> 00:03:08,800
Right before we entered the water,

54
00:03:16,639 --> 00:03:17,319
Shu Tong.

55
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:19,479
Shu Tong!

56
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,120
What are you looking at?

57
00:03:36,879 --> 00:03:38,719
A flood's coming, everyone move!

58
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,240
What are you all standing around for?

59
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,560
Run!

60
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:43,680
Move it, everyone!

61
00:03:44,879 --> 00:03:45,680
There's no time!

62
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,439
The flood's coming, hurry up!

63
00:03:49,039 --> 00:03:49,919
Get moving!

64
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:51,719
Once she calmed down, I turned around,

65
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:53,639
and every one of you was staggering all over.

66
00:03:53,639 --> 00:03:54,599
Ridiculous.

67
00:03:54,919 --> 00:03:57,039
It must have been from inhaling the toxic spores.

68
00:03:57,280 --> 00:03:59,199
Everyone got poisoned to varying degrees.

69
00:03:59,599 --> 00:04:01,159
The hallucination I had just now

70
00:04:01,719 --> 00:04:03,039
was absolutely terrifying.

71
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:06,719
Guess what I hallucinated.

72
00:04:06,919 --> 00:04:07,719
What?

73
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,759
Braised offal stew,

74
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,680
stir-fried liver,

75
00:04:13,599 --> 00:04:14,439
boiled tripe,

76
00:04:15,159 --> 00:04:16,040
mutton hotpot.

77
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:19,519
All floating right in front of me,

78
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,680
and I couldn't grab a single one.

79
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,160
Now tell me that's not terrifying.

80
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:23,920
Even without being poisoned,

81
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,439
don't you fantasize about that stuff anyway?

82
00:04:27,079 --> 00:04:27,879
Advisor He,

83
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:29,680
what did you hallucinate?

84
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:32,319
A serpent monster.

85
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,839
I saw some kind of

86
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,959
fire-breathing salamander.

87
00:04:38,959 --> 00:04:40,360
Then that doesn't make sense.

88
00:04:40,959 --> 00:04:42,279
You see, all of us,

89
00:04:42,279 --> 00:04:44,319
because of the places we've been,

90
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,519
and what we've seen,

91
00:04:45,519 --> 00:04:46,680
form an image of fear

92
00:04:46,680 --> 00:04:48,199
deep in our subconscious.

93
00:04:48,199 --> 00:04:49,639
That's what we end up seeing.

94
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:53,680
I don't know, I'm not sure either.

95
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:57,639
Fatty.

96
00:04:58,920 --> 00:04:59,560
Scout ahead.

97
00:05:00,360 --> 00:05:01,720
Wait, me again?

98
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:02,759
Hurry up.

99
00:05:05,399 --> 00:05:06,839
Clap your hands together,

100
00:05:07,959 --> 00:05:09,800
on the first day of the first month.

101
00:05:20,079 --> 00:05:21,720
In that hallucination of yours,

102
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:24,639
you saw more than just the serpent, right?

103
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:25,959
What do you mean?

104
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:29,639
From your unnatural expression earlier,

105
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,560
I have reason to suspect

106
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:33,720
that I appeared in your hallucination.

107
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:36,879
I didn't realize you'd become so narcissistic.

108
00:05:37,279 --> 00:05:38,000
Let me ask you,

109
00:05:38,399 --> 00:05:39,120
just now,

110
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:40,959
did you really not have any hallucinations?

111
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,319
Mine is just capillary hyperplasia,

112
00:05:43,639 --> 00:05:44,959
not a radar signal.

113
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:45,959
What could I possibly feel?

114
00:05:47,839 --> 00:05:50,399
But before, in Yunling and Nanyun,

115
00:05:50,839 --> 00:05:52,560
the Lingxiao Pearl

116
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,600
stimulated your brain waves, causing hallucinations.

117
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,120
So I suspect

118
00:05:56,839 --> 00:05:58,199
we might not be poisoned.

119
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,600
Rather, deep within Mengna Valley,

120
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,000
there's some kind of substance

121
00:06:02,279 --> 00:06:03,839
that stimulates our brain waves,

122
00:06:04,079 --> 00:06:05,240
thus producing hallucinations.

123
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,720
So you suspect

124
00:06:08,319 --> 00:06:10,519
the disappearance of the Mengna Valley civilization

125
00:06:11,439 --> 00:06:13,040
is related to these hallucinations?

126
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,680
The sudden disappearance of ancient civilizations

127
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,120
is usually linked to sudden plagues,

128
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:21,360
climate change, or foreign invasion.

129
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,879
The epic poem Dawang gave me mentioned

130
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,160
that Mengna Valley,

131
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:27,079
due to its expansion

132
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:28,759
and oppression of surrounding regions,

133
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,199
once triggered uprisings and campaigns against it.

134
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,079
But when they gathered together

135
00:06:33,079 --> 00:06:35,040
and arrived at Mengna Valley, they found

136
00:06:35,079 --> 00:06:37,319
that Mengna Valley had suddenly vanished overnight.

137
00:06:37,879 --> 00:06:39,759
The poem mentions no plague

138
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:40,959
or climate change,

139
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,839
and the war had not even begun.

140
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,759
So I'm wondering,

141
00:06:44,959 --> 00:06:46,680
what exactly caused

142
00:06:46,839 --> 00:06:47,920
their destruction?

143
00:06:50,519 --> 00:06:52,120
The Mengna Valley civilization

144
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:57,040
began with that sacred pearl in the queen's hand.

145
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,519
So that sacred pearl

146
00:06:58,519 --> 00:07:00,319
is most likely the Lingxiao Pearl.

147
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:01,879
Do you think all of this

148
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,720
might have also ended because of it?

149
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,560
It seems only by finding the Lingxiao Pearl

150
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,720
can we uncover the truth.

151
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:11,560
Exactly.

152
00:07:11,879 --> 00:07:12,839
You know what, I think

153
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,279
there's really something off about you.

154
00:07:15,879 --> 00:07:17,560
Ever since you woke up,

155
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,319
you've been constantly on edge.

156
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,439
What are you thinking about?

157
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,519
I think I

158
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,639
remembered the scene of my parents' car accident.

159
00:07:27,519 --> 00:07:29,160
But I don't know if it's real.

160
00:07:30,319 --> 00:07:31,800
Still, for things like this,

161
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,279
it's better to forget.

162
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:36,399
If you really want to know what happened,

163
00:07:36,399 --> 00:07:38,680
the best way is to find a witness.

164
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:41,600
Track them down, compare both sides,

165
00:07:41,879 --> 00:07:44,040
and you'll know exactly what happened.

166
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,959
But this witness,

167
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,759
where am I supposed to find them?

168
00:07:49,360 --> 00:07:52,240
Yeah, after all these years,

169
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,680
where could you find them?

170
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:55,199
Found it!

171
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,079
Old Chen, I found it!

172
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,639
Old Chen, I found it!

173
00:08:03,439 --> 00:08:04,480
Right up ahead!

174
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:06,600
Over there!

175
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:31,800
Go up, go up, just head up there!

176
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,120
Old Chen.

177
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,159
The eyeball pattern.

178
00:08:59,759 --> 00:09:00,559
Yeah.

179
00:09:00,799 --> 00:09:01,679
This pattern...

180
00:09:01,679 --> 00:09:03,399
is in the Baoji Hero's Epic Scroll.

181
00:09:03,399 --> 00:09:04,320
It was mentioned in there.

182
00:09:04,759 --> 00:09:06,960
Nebulae surrounding the
serpent god's demonic eye.

183
00:09:07,399 --> 00:09:10,159
They called it Xuanlei
Black Crystal Mountain.

184
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,679
Never mind what mountain it is.

185
00:09:12,879 --> 00:09:14,200
Figuring it out is what matters.

186
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:15,960
Remember the Bingpo
Domain-Quelling Mountain?

187
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:18,080
Sounds like a mountain, but
it was actually a wolf.

188
00:09:18,879 --> 00:09:20,559
This isn't a mountain or a wolf.

189
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:23,240
It's a tunnel leading
to the altar grounds.

190
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,399
The altar grounds.

191
00:09:26,759 --> 00:09:28,559
Xuan... what does Xuanlei mean?

192
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:30,960
If this is really the path
to the altar grounds,

193
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:33,639
it must relate to the Mengna Valley
ceremonial rites.

194
00:09:33,879 --> 00:09:36,200
Xuanlei is likely a mechanism
to punish those

195
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,519
who intrude during the ceremony.

196
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,720
These symbols on the door...

197
00:09:52,559 --> 00:09:53,320
Miss He,

198
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:56,600
could these possibly be numbers?

199
00:09:56,919 --> 00:09:57,639
Exactly.

200
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,159
Dots and dashes.

201
00:09:59,159 --> 00:10:00,200
They can be combined freely

202
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:01,559
to form different numbers.

203
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:05,960
Hey, why is sand flowing here?

204
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:09,320
Look! What is that?

205
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,960
We triggered a trap, didn't we?

206
00:10:24,279 --> 00:10:25,480
Get back, hurry!

207
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,600
A trap?

208
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:32,200
Don't panic.

209
00:10:32,759 --> 00:10:33,960
We must have triggered

210
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:35,200
the door's linked mechanism.

211
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:37,039
If we solve this puzzle correctly,

212
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:37,960
the arrows won't fire.

213
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,840
Now we even have a shield umbrella.

214
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,039
Why aren't we opening the door yet?

215
00:10:41,039 --> 00:10:41,919
What's the rush?

216
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,759
Based on Fatty's years of
trap-triggering experience,

217
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:53,200
I think these arrows

218
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,679
won't be firing anytime soon.

219
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:55,840
You all find cover first.

220
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,919
I'll give it a try.

221
00:10:56,919 --> 00:10:57,639
Okay, alright.

222
00:10:57,639 --> 00:10:58,399
I'll go with you.

223
00:10:58,960 --> 00:10:59,639
It's fine.

224
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,720
Leave the Vajra umbrella with me.

225
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,840
Take good care of Old Lu.

226
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:04,159
You be careful out there.

227
00:11:05,279 --> 00:11:06,480
Go, take the umbrella, take it.

228
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:08,360
Fall back!

229
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:37,080
Uncle Min, what's he going up there for?

230
00:11:37,399 --> 00:11:39,720
You always hide in the back when
danger appears.

231
00:11:39,720 --> 00:11:41,279
This time you rushed to the front line.

232
00:11:42,799 --> 00:11:44,200
Either you've lost your mind,

233
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:46,200
or you've got a plan up your sleeve.

234
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:48,679
Brother Chen, let me tell you,

235
00:11:49,559 --> 00:11:51,879
the Mengna Valley worshipped queens.

236
00:11:52,279 --> 00:11:53,519
The queen passed her throne

237
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,759
to one who resembled her.

238
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,039
Power passed down through generations,

239
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:01,519
showcasing the queen's eternal rule.

240
00:12:01,799 --> 00:12:02,759
What is this?

241
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,679
This is a grand cycle of reincarnation.

242
00:12:05,200 --> 00:12:06,080
Look here.

243
00:12:07,279 --> 00:12:08,320
Six sides.

244
00:12:09,639 --> 00:12:11,240
Do you think it's a coincidence,

245
00:12:11,519 --> 00:12:14,799
or does it hint at the Six
Paths of Reincarnation?

246
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:17,759
An Xiang,

247
00:12:18,559 --> 00:12:19,960
you don't look so well.

248
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,039
Are you feeling unwell?

249
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:25,600
Maybe it's the long journey,

250
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,120
just running out of energy.

251
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:29,000
I watched you grow up.

252
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:30,440
Whether you're physically unwell

253
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:31,879
or have something on your mind,

254
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,600
I can still tell clearly.

255
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,159
True.

256
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:38,600
You, Aunt He, and Godfather

257
00:12:39,559 --> 00:12:41,399
have watched me every step of the way.

258
00:12:41,600 --> 00:12:42,279
Of course.

259
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:44,159
Your adoption paperwork

260
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:45,480
was all handled by me personally.

261
00:12:50,919 --> 00:12:52,600
Then in my file records,

262
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,799
is there information
about my parents?

263
00:12:57,440 --> 00:12:58,720
If I tell you,

264
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,000
Uncle Min will definitely
be very unhappy.

265
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:03,360
So you do know.

266
00:13:04,879 --> 00:13:06,399
What exactly do you want to know?

267
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,960
I want to know about my parents.

268
00:13:09,759 --> 00:13:11,120
And whether my parents also had

269
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:13,519
an eyeball scar on them.

270
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:44,240
Old Chen is really something.

271
00:13:44,759 --> 00:13:45,799
Come on, let's go up.

272
00:13:45,799 --> 00:13:46,440
Move!

273
00:14:11,039 --> 00:14:12,039
Hey, Brother Chen.

274
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,480
Could this really be

275
00:14:14,879 --> 00:14:16,879
Xuanlei Black Crystal Mountain?

276
00:14:21,320 --> 00:14:22,679
It's not black at all.

277
00:14:27,519 --> 00:14:28,159
A door.
